# AI Tools project

## What this repo is

- **Next.js App Router** app: directory (tools/videos), notes, prompts, news, admin (Supabase-backed).
- **`assistant/` (Python FastAPI)** is a **separate project** on your machine. Do not move its backend into this repo unless the user explicitly asks for a full merge.

## Personal assistant touchpoints (when editing)

- URL helpers: `lib/assistant-urls.ts` (`getAssistantDashboardUrl`, `getAssistantOpenApiUrl`, `DEFAULT_ASSISTANT_DASHBOARD`).
- **Env:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_ASSISTANT_DASHBOARD_URL` — required for non-default dashboard host (e.g. Tailscale `http://100.x.x.x:8000/dashboard`). Client-only; rebuild after changes.
- **Routes:** `app/assistant/` (admin-only embedded view + fallbacks). **Admin:** Personal control opens a **named popup** (`assistant-personal`) via `window.open`, not an in-page tab.
- **Nav:** `components/NavLinks.tsx` — Assistant link is **admin-only**.
- **Secrets:** Never commit service account / credential JSON. `.gitignore` includes `ai-tools-*.json`.

## Implementation habits

- Match existing patterns: `components/ui/*`, `@/lib/*`, Supabase via `@/lib/supabase`, client auth via `AuthSessionProvider` / `useAuthSession`.
- Prefer small, focused diffs; avoid drive-by refactors and unsolicited markdown docs.

## Shipping

- Follow `.cursor/rules/deploy-after-change.mdc`: after substantive changes, `npm run build` (fix failures), then commit and `git push origin main` for Vercel (no manual `vercel deploy`).
